WEBVTT

00:04.229 --> 00:05.678
Sure was sweet of
the neighbors to let us

00:05.679 --> 00:07.848
piggyback onto
their garage sale.

00:07.849 --> 00:08.968
They didn't <i>let </i> us.

00:08.969 --> 00:11.388
I just started throwing
crap on their lawn.

00:11.389 --> 00:13.388
They're too polite to say no.

00:13.389 --> 00:17.348
It's the one up-side of having
religious nuts as neighbors.

00:17.349 --> 00:19.678
Mom, just because people
smile and wave at us,

00:19.679 --> 00:22.098
does not make them
religious nuts.

00:22.099 --> 00:25.058
Hmm. Either way, the meek
are about to inherit

00:25.059 --> 00:27.729
a big ball of tangled
Christmas lights.

00:28.729 --> 00:29.928
Well, that's how
we're gonna play it,

00:29.929 --> 00:32.728
let's giveth unto them
Mike's old snow tires.

00:32.729 --> 00:33.728
Gangway!

00:33.729 --> 00:35.678
Starboard!
Starboard!

00:35.679 --> 00:37.348
Starboard!
Starboard!

00:37.349 --> 00:38.768
On my starboard
or your starboard?

00:38.769 --> 00:41.453
Whichever one doesn't crush
my barnacles against the wall!

00:43.269 --> 00:45.639
Guess what I bought
from the religious nuts?

00:47.099 --> 00:48.638
You got to be kidding me, Vin.

00:48.639 --> 00:50.268
I want that eyesore out of here.

00:50.269 --> 00:51.348
Hold on, Joyce.

00:51.349 --> 00:52.768
You got to picture
it all fixed up,

00:52.769 --> 00:56.179
with me on deck in my Speedo,
like Aristotle Onassis.

00:57.389 --> 00:58.848
Couldn't you have stopped him?

00:58.849 --> 01:00.018
You've seen him in that Speedo.

01:00.019 --> 01:01.428
Oh, I tried to
talk him out of it,

01:01.429 --> 01:02.558
but he made
a very good argument.

01:02.559 --> 01:03.558
What?

01:03.559 --> 01:05.639
I get to be first mate.

